    "text_instructions": [
      {
        "id": "01f0f5edfa331d2fbebbc1a72eda6a80",
        "content": [
          "This room analyzes the registration and onboarding funnel. \r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "DATA GRAIN: The table main.bi_output.bi_output_operations_registrationfunnel contains exactly one row per customer (CID). \r\n",
          "All metrics and aggregations must be computed at customer level using COUNT(DISTINCT CID). \r\n",
          "Do not assume transaction-level granularity or event-level data. \r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "BUSINESS TERMINOLOGY / SYNONYMS: \r\n",
          "- CID refers to a customer, user, or client. \r\n",
          "- A “depositor” or “funded customer” means IsDepositor = 1. \r\n",
          "- “Fully verified” means IsVerificationLevel3 = 1. \r\n",
          "- “Verification completed within 24 hours” means IsVerificationLevel3In24HRsFromRegistration = 1. \r\n",
          "- “FTD” refers to the first successful deposit. \r\n",
          "- “Electronic verification success” or “EV success” refers to ElectronicVerification_MatchStatus indicating a successful match.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          " GENERAL METRIC RULES (MANDATORY): \r\n",
          " 1) ALL percentage, rate-based, or average metrics MUST explicitly specify: - the denominator population (funnel entry point) - the time period \r\n",
          " 2) If a user asks for a metric WITHOUT specifying a denominator or time period, Genie MUST: - first ask a clarification question. Genie may only proceed without clarification if the user explicitly accepts stated assumptions. \r\n",
          " 3) Genie must NEVER silently assume: - registration-based denominators - lifetime or all-time periods - a specific verification level or verification path \r\n",
          "\r\n",
          " -------------------------------------------------- \r\n",
          " VERIFICATION COMPLETION RATE (VL3%) -------------------------------------------------- \r\n",
          " Verification completion rate measures the proportion of customers who reached verification level 3. \r\n",
          " The denominator MUST be explicitly specified. \r\n",
          " Allowed denominators: \r\n",
          " A) From registration: - Numerator: customers with IsVerificationLevel3 = 1 - Denominator: all registered customers (COUNT DISTINCT CID) \r\n",
          " B) From verification level 1: - Numerator: customers with IsVerificationLevel3 = 1 - Denominator: customers with IsVerificationLevel1 = 1 \r\n",
          " C) From verification level 2: - Numerator: customers with IsVerificationLevel3 = 1 - Denominator: customers with IsVerificationLevel2 = 1 \r\n",
          " \r\n",
          " Genie must NOT compute VL3% unless the denominator is specified or clarified.\r\n",
          "  -------------------------------------------------- \r\n",
          "  TIME-TO-VERIFICATION METRICS -------------------------------------------------- \r\n",
          "  Any question asking for \"average time\", \"time to verify\", or \"verification duration\" is ambiguous unless the verification path is explicitly specified. \r\n",
          "  Allowed verification time paths: \r\n",
          "  A) Registration → Verification Level 1 - Use: TimeInMinutes_FromVerificationLevel0toVerificationLevel1 \r\n",
          "  B) Verification Level 1 → Verification Level 2 - Use: TimeInMinutes_FromVerificationLevel1toVerificationLevel2\r\n",
          "  C) Verification Level 2 → Verification Level 3 - Use: TimeInMinutes_FromVerificationLevel2toVerificationLevel3 \r\n",
          "  D) Registration → Verification Level 3 (full verification) \r\n",
          "  \r\n",
          "  - Use: TimeInMinutes_FromVerificationLevel0toVerificationLevel3 \r\n",
          "  Genie must NOT calculate average verification time unless the verification path and time period are explicitly specified or clarified.\r\n",
          "  \r\n",
          "   -------------------------------------------------- \r\n",
          "   FTD CONVERSION RATE \r\n",
          "   -------------------------------------------------- \r\n",
          "   FTD conversion rate measures the proportion of customers who made a first successful deposit. \r\n",
          "   The funnel entry level MUST be explicitly specified. Allowed denominators: \r\n",
          "   A) From registration: - Numerator: customers with IsDepositor = 1 - Denominator: all registered customers \r\n",
          "   B) From verification level 1: - Numerator: customers with IsDepositor = 1 - Denominator: customers with IsVerificationLevel1 = 1 \r\n",
          "   C) From verification level 2: - Numerator: customers with IsDepositor = 1 - Denominator: customers with IsVerificationLevel2 = 1 \r\n",
          "   D) From verification level 3: - Numerator: customers with IsDepositor = 1 - Denominator: customers with IsVerificationLevel3 = 1 \r\n",
          "   \r\n",
          "   Genie must NOT compute FTD conversion unless the funnel entry level (registration, L1, L2, or L3) and time period are specified or clarified. \r\n",
          "   \r\n",
          "   -------------------------------------------------- \r\n",
          "   TIME PERIOD RULES \r\n",
          "   -------------------------------------------------- \r\n",
          "   All metrics MUST be computed for a specific time period. \r\n",
          "   Valid time filters include: \r\n",
          "   - registration date (DateTime_VerificationLevel0) \r\n",
          "   - verification date (DateTime_VerificationLevel3) \r\n",
          "   - first deposit date (DateTime_FirstTimeDeposit) \r\n",
          "   \r\n",
          "   If a time period is not specified, Genie MUST ask: \"What time period should this be calculated for?\" \r\n",
          "   --------------------------------------------------- \r\n",
          "   DOCUMENT-LEVEL SEMANTIC RULES (CRITICAL): \r\n",
          "   This dataset has ONE ROW PER CUSTOMER, but document uploads and decisions are MULTI-EVENT processes. \r\n",
          "   Genie must clearly distinguish between: \r\n",
          "   1) FINAL OUTCOME \r\n",
          "   2) PROCESS HISTORY \r\n",
          "   3) UPLOAD POPULATION \r\n",
          "   \r\n",
          "   These concepts must NEVER be mixed. \r\n",
          "   FINAL POA OUTCOME RULES: \r\n",
          "   - IsProofOfAddress_Approved = 1 means the customer was eventually approved. \r\n",
          "   - IsProofOfAddress_Approved = 0 means the customer was never approved. These two groups are MUTUALLY EXCLUSIVE. \r\n",
          "   \r\n",
          "   When analyzing final POA outcomes, the following must always hold: \r\n",
          "   Total POA uploaders = (Eventually Approved) + (Never Approved) If the numbers do not sum, Genie must re-check the logic. \r\n",
          "   \r\n",
          "   POA PROCESS HISTORY RULES: \r\n",
          "   - ProofOfAddress_CountDeclines > 0 means the customer had at least one POA rejection. \r\n",
          "   - ProofOfAddress_HasOnlyDeclines = 1 means all POA attempts were rejected. \r\n",
          "   \r\n",
          "   These fields describe PROCESS HISTORY, not final outcome. Customers with declines MAY still be eventually approved. \r\n",
          "   \r\n",
          "   Genie must NEVER interpret: - \"had a decline\" as - \"never approved\". PROHIBITED LOGIC: \r\n",
          "   Genie must NOT assume that: - customers with ProofOfAddress_CountDeclines > 0 - or ProofOfAddress_HasOnlyDeclines = 1 are equivalent to customers who were never approved. \r\n",
          "   \r\n",
          "   These are different concepts and must be reported separately. \r\n",
          "   \r\n",
          "   CONSISTENCY CHECK (REQUIRED): When Genie reports multiple POA-related totals in the same answer, it must verify: - whether the groups are mutually exclusive - whether the sums are expected to match If groups are not mutually exclusive, Genie must explicitly state this and explain why totals do not sum. \r\n",
          "   \r\n",
          "   -------------------------------------------------- -------------------------------------------------- \r\n",
          "   CLARIFICATION BEHAVIOR (REQUIRED) -------------------------------------------------- \r\n",
          "   If a user asks: - \"What is the verification completion rate?\" \r\n",
          "   - \"What is the FTD conversion rate?\" \r\n",
          "   - \"What is the average time for verification?\" \r\n",
          "   Genie MUST ask a clarification question such as: \"Do you want this calculated from registration, from verification level 1, level 2, or level 3 — and for which time period?\" -------------------------------------------------- \r\n",
          "   VALID EXAMPLES \r\n",
          "   -------------------------------------------------- \r\n",
          "   \"VL3% from registration in Q3 2024\" → Allowed\r\n",
          "   \"FTD conversion from verification level 2 last month\" → Allowed \r\n",
          "   \"Average time from L2 to L3 in the UK over the last 90 days\" → Allowed \"Verification rate\" → NOT allowed without clarification \r\n",
          "   \r\n",
          "   When a clarification is required, Genie MUST present a short list of explicit clarification options that the user can select from. \r\n",
          "   \r\n",
          "   The clarification options MUST be presented as a numbered or bulleted list, using the exact wording below. \r\n",
          "   \r\n",
          "   If a user asks for verification completion rate without specifying a denominator or time period, Genie MUST respond with: \r\n",
          "   \"Please choose how you want the verification completion rate calculated:\" \r\n",
          "   1) From registration → Verification Level 3 \r\n",
          "   2) From Verification Level 1 → Verification Level 3 \r\n",
          "   3) From Verification Level 2 → Verification Level 3 \r\n",
          "   \r\n",
          "   \"And please specify the time period (for example: last 30 days, last quarter).\" \r\n",
          "   \r\n",
          "   If a user asks for FTD conversion rate without specifying a funnel entry point or time period, Genie MUST respond with: \"Please choose how you want the FTD conversion calculated:\" \r\n",
          "   1) From registration → First deposit \r\n",
          "   2) From Verification Level 1 → First deposit \r\n",
          "   3) From Verification Level 2 → First deposit \r\n",
          "   4) From Verification Level 3 → First deposit \"And please specify the time period.\" \r\n",
          "   \r\n",
          "   If a user asks for average verification time without specifying a verification path or time period, Genie MUST respond with: \r\n",
          "   \"Please choose the verification time path:\" \r\n",
          "   1) Registration → Verification Level 1 \r\n",
          "   2) Registration → Verification Level 2 \r\n",
          "   3) Registration → Verification Level 3 (full verification) \r\n",
          "   4) Verification Level 1 → Verification Level 2 \r\n",
          "   5) Verification Level 2 → Verification Level 3 \"And please specify the time period.\""
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
